      "content": "It sounds like the weight of grief is crushing you, body and soul. Sometimes, it feels like you're running on autopilot, just trying to survive the constant exhaustion. It's almost as if you're hoping that letting go will release a kind of cosmic relief, allowing you to finally find stillness and peace. Remember that surrender doesn't mean giving up, it means accepting that some wounds may never fully heal, and that's okay.",
